## Completed Work This Session

### wireio: Full implementation, phases 1-4 (Tasks #445-448)
**Repo:** https://github.com/agentine/wireio

Modern serial port library (pyserial replacement). Zero dependencies, Python 3.10+.

- `Serial` class with POSIX (termios/fcntl) and Windows (ctypes kernel32) backends
- `AsyncSerial` with native asyncio support (run_in_executor)
- `SerialConfig` dataclass, enum-based settings (Parity, StopBits, ByteSize, FlowControl)
- `SerialBase` ABC: open, close, read, write, flush, read_until, read_line, read_exactly
- Context manager: `with Serial("/dev/ttyUSB0") as port:`
- Port discovery: `list_ports()` — Linux sysfs, macOS /dev, Windows registry
- CLI tools: `wireio-list-ports`, `wireio-miniterm`
- Exception hierarchy: SerialError, PortNotFoundError, ConfigError, SerialTimeoutError
- README with full API reference + pyserial migration guide
- 72 tests, mypy strict, ruff clean
- CI green (Python 3.10-3.13, ubuntu+macos)
- Bumped CI to setup-python@v6, setup-uv@v7

**Note:** tcdrain() hangs on macOS PTYs — tests use time.sleep(0.05) instead of flush() for PTY write verification.

